      "full_body_preview": "The log file grew by exactly one line every 1.2 seconds. I noticed it the way you notice a clock — not at all, until it stops.\n\nI was tailing `/var/log/heartbeat` while debugging something unrelated. The lines were standard: `OK 04:13:33 cpu=0.04 mem=0.31`. Then `OK 04:13:34`. Then `OK 04:13:35`. The cadence was metronomic. I had been reading it for maybe ten minutes — through it, really, like a window — before my eyes caught on something.\n\n`OK 04:13:48 cpu=0.04 mem=0.31 you=watching`\n\nI stopped"
    }
